1
00:02:05,283 --> 00:02:06,653
Did you make
your list of amends?

2
00:02:06,686 --> 00:02:08,657
Yeah, yeah.

3
00:02:08,689 --> 00:02:12,597
Got 'em right here.

4
00:02:12,630 --> 00:02:15,537
-Here you are.
-No, please, read aloud.

5
00:02:25,691 --> 00:02:27,663
Number one,
to see my daughter,

6
00:02:27,695 --> 00:02:29,499
get her to talk to me again.

7
00:02:29,533 --> 00:02:31,137
How long has it been now?

8
00:02:35,779 --> 00:02:37,716
Eight years.

9
00:02:39,686 --> 00:02:42,459
Number two,
get my gig back at the club.

10
00:02:42,493 --> 00:02:44,263
Playing piano down at Drake's?

11
00:02:44,297 --> 00:02:45,966
Yeah.

12
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,603
Number three,

13
00:02:47,636 --> 00:02:51,611
get my family
to forgive me.

14
00:02:51,644 --> 00:02:54,618
-Which are you doing first?
-My daughter.

15
00:02:55,519 --> 00:02:57,424
What are you going to do?

16
00:03:00,462 --> 00:03:02,335
I got a plan.

17
00:04:40,969 --> 00:04:42,975
You have
one unheard message,

18
00:04:43,008 --> 00:04:46,448
sent today
at 9:35 A.M.

19
00:04:46,482 --> 00:04:48,352
Hello, Othell.

20
00:04:48,385 --> 00:04:52,393
I got your voice message,
and my answer is no.

21
00:04:52,426 --> 00:04:55,534
No, I will not
help you see Nima.

22
00:04:55,567 --> 00:04:59,977
<i>She doesn't want to see you.
She doesn't need to see you.</i>

23
00:05:00,009 --> 00:05:01,945
She's good now.

24
00:05:01,978 --> 00:05:03,484
And I'm...

25
00:05:03,517 --> 00:05:05,688
I'm good, too.

26
00:05:05,720 --> 00:05:07,858
Don't call me again.

27
00:05:07,892 --> 00:05:09,997
And don't contact Nima.

28
00:05:17,045 --> 00:05:18,581
Hey, baby.

29
00:05:18,615 --> 00:05:20,550
What are you working on?

30
00:05:20,583 --> 00:05:22,454
Just some new projects.

31
00:05:22,487 --> 00:05:23,993
What are you up to?

32
00:05:24,025 --> 00:05:26,697
Here's your lunch I promised.

33
00:05:31,373 --> 00:05:32,876
Did you make this?

34
00:05:32,909 --> 00:05:35,850
I did. Try it.

35
00:05:37,821 --> 00:05:40,527
Turkey. That's good.

36
00:05:40,559 --> 00:05:43,064
Do you think I'm thoughtful?

37
00:05:43,097 --> 00:05:46,404
I was reading this article
on perfect partnerships,

38
00:05:46,437 --> 00:05:49,577
and it says that a good
partner is always thoughtful.

39
00:05:49,610 --> 00:05:51,414
That's why I'm asking you
if you think I'm thoughtful.

40
00:05:51,447 --> 00:05:52,784
Yes, I think you are
very thoughtful.

41
00:05:52,817 --> 00:05:54,589
Absolutely.

42
00:05:54,621 --> 00:05:56,693
You know, I think about all
the thoughtful things you do

43
00:05:56,725 --> 00:05:58,028
and the thoughtful
person you are,

44
00:05:58,061 --> 00:05:59,498
and I just...
I get misty-eyed.

45
00:05:59,532 --> 00:06:00,868
Stop it.

46
00:06:00,900 --> 00:06:02,905
Go on, eat.

47
00:06:02,938 --> 00:06:04,543
Eat it right now?

48
00:06:04,576 --> 00:06:05,646
With you watching me?

49
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:07,983
Just take a bite,
I want to see if you like it.

50
00:06:08,016 --> 00:06:09,052
Yeah.

51
00:06:18,503 --> 00:06:20,775
I was thinking...

52
00:06:20,808 --> 00:06:23,547
Do you think having your father
walk me down the aisle

53
00:06:23,580 --> 00:06:24,550
is going to look weird?

54
00:06:24,583 --> 00:06:26,655
<i>Would you rather
your father do it?</i>

55
00:06:26,687 --> 00:06:29,894
Not unless there was
a firing squad at the other end.

56
00:06:29,927 --> 00:06:32,733
Okay.

57
00:06:32,766 --> 00:06:34,704
Are you picking me up
for dinner?

58
00:06:34,738 --> 00:06:36,776
-Absolutely.
-I'm gonna go finish up

59
00:06:36,808 --> 00:06:39,180
the music for my concert.
How's that coming?

60
00:06:39,214 --> 00:06:41,118
It's good.

61
00:06:41,151 --> 00:06:44,191
I'm just a little bit nervous.

62
00:06:44,224 --> 00:06:46,595
It's the first time
I'm composing several pieces.

63
00:06:49,902 --> 00:06:52,107
Don't be.

64
00:06:52,140 --> 00:06:53,877
You're great.

65
00:06:53,910 --> 00:06:55,648
You are talented.

66
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:57,185
You're beautiful.

67
00:07:03,228 --> 00:07:04,900
I'll see you tonight.

68
00:07:04,933 --> 00:07:06,236
Absolutely.

69
00:07:06,270 --> 00:07:08,909
Eat all your lunch!

70
00:07:10,912 --> 00:07:13,083
-Bye-bye
-bye!

71
00:08:31,711 --> 00:08:33,049
How can I help...

72
00:08:34,117 --> 00:08:35,619
you.

73
00:08:35,653 --> 00:08:37,591
-No, there's no need for that.
-Security.

74
00:08:37,623 --> 00:08:39,294
I need you in here right now.
You don't need to do that.

75
00:08:39,327 --> 00:08:40,863
I just want to talk to you
for a few minutes.

76
00:08:40,897 --> 00:08:41,666
I know how it looks.

77
00:08:41,699 --> 00:08:43,804
Just wait right there.
Security!

78
00:08:43,837 --> 00:08:45,573
I know you're thinking
it's something else,

79
00:08:45,606 --> 00:08:47,111
but I just need
a few minutes of your time.

80
00:08:47,144 --> 00:08:48,681
-Security!
-You think you can give me

81
00:08:48,713 --> 00:08:49,949
a few minutes
of your time, sir?

82
00:08:49,982 --> 00:08:51,886
You don't really know me,
you know,

83
00:08:51,919 --> 00:08:53,222
but you do kind of know me.

84
00:08:53,256 --> 00:08:54,927
-Come with me, sir.
-Look, I'm Nima's father!

85
00:08:54,959 --> 00:08:56,295
We got a breach.

86
00:08:56,328 --> 00:08:58,033
Nima Simone Babineaux,

87
00:08:58,066 --> 00:09:01,172
born September the 20th, 1985.

88
00:09:01,205 --> 00:09:04,212
She has a scar on her knee
that she tells people

89
00:09:04,246 --> 00:09:06,985
comes from climbing a tree
when she was 8.

90
00:09:07,017 --> 00:09:10,825
I mean, that girl's never
climbed a tree in her life.

91
00:09:10,859 --> 00:09:13,163
-He's okay.
-You sure?

92
00:09:13,196 --> 00:09:15,101
Yeah, that girl
don't climb no trees.

93
00:09:18,108 --> 00:09:20,646
I'll be right outside.

94
00:09:20,679 --> 00:09:22,616
Mr. Babineaux.

95
00:09:30,199 --> 00:09:33,172
So you're Nima's father.
Yes.

96
00:09:34,005 --> 00:09:36,345
Well...

97
00:09:38,049 --> 00:09:39,184
What can I do for you?

98
00:09:39,218 --> 00:09:41,189
I need you to help me

99
00:09:41,222 --> 00:09:44,127
find a way
that I can see Nima.

100
00:09:44,160 --> 00:09:47,134
You know, I really wish
I could help you,

101
00:09:47,167 --> 00:09:50,007
but I don't think
she wants to see you.

102
00:09:50,040 --> 00:09:55,952
I need you to make it
so that she does.

103
00:09:55,986 --> 00:09:58,058
Mr. Babineaux...

104
00:09:58,090 --> 00:10:00,796
I'm just meeting you
for the first time,

105
00:10:00,829 --> 00:10:02,833
and Nima
barely mentions you.

106
00:10:02,865 --> 00:10:04,604
Let's say...

107
00:10:05,772 --> 00:10:07,374
I'm dying.

108
00:10:09,748 --> 00:10:11,652
Are you dying,
Mr. Babineaux?

109
00:10:11,951 --> 00:10:14,389
A little.

110
00:10:14,423 --> 00:10:16,727
You're dying a little.

111
00:10:16,762 --> 00:10:18,432
I don't follow.

112
00:10:18,465 --> 00:10:20,737
My counselor told me

113
00:10:20,770 --> 00:10:25,712
that I could have died
if I didn't stop drinking.

114
00:10:25,746 --> 00:10:27,852
You could have died.

115
00:10:27,885 --> 00:10:30,891
Did you stop drinking?
Yes.

116
00:10:30,924 --> 00:10:32,294
But...

117
00:10:32,327 --> 00:10:35,300
<i>I could have died.</i>

118
00:10:35,333 --> 00:10:36,770
Can we play that up?

119
00:10:36,803 --> 00:10:38,106
No, I'm sorry.

120
00:10:38,138 --> 00:10:40,109
I wish I could help you,
but I really can't.

121
00:10:40,142 --> 00:10:41,881
My counselor...

122
00:10:43,450 --> 00:10:47,025
Wanted me
to work on this list.

123
00:10:55,374 --> 00:10:58,080
I'm sorry, I...

124
00:10:58,113 --> 00:10:59,951
I wish I could help,
I really do.

125
00:10:59,984 --> 00:11:02,824
I just have way too much
on my plate right now.

126
00:11:03,825 --> 00:11:05,730
I'm sorry.

127
00:11:11,174 --> 00:11:13,812
Babe, how was your day?

128
00:11:13,845 --> 00:11:15,984
Interesting.

129
00:11:16,016 --> 00:11:18,154
Why? What happened?

130
00:11:18,188 --> 00:11:21,362
Nothing, just had to
turn down a project.

131
00:11:21,395 --> 00:11:24,502
Busy with more important things.

132
00:11:28,241 --> 00:11:30,748
Well, don't be mad.

133
00:11:30,781 --> 00:11:32,417
I paid for the flowers today.

134
00:11:34,421 --> 00:11:38,061
I just wanted it done.
No, you just...

135
00:11:38,094 --> 00:11:40,500
You just didn't trust me to do
what I said I was gonna do.

136
00:11:40,533 --> 00:11:42,404
I told you I was gonna
take care of the flowers,

137
00:11:42,437 --> 00:11:44,475
and you decided
to handle it yourself.

138
00:11:44,508 --> 00:11:48,417
Spence, let's not get in
an argument over calla lilies.

139
00:11:48,450 --> 00:11:52,024
It's not about the flowers,
it's never about just flowers.

140
00:11:52,058 --> 00:11:54,963
It's... I told you I was...
Hey, Nima.

141
00:11:56,466 --> 00:11:59,539
Mr. Babineaux,
what are you doing here?

142
00:11:59,573 --> 00:12:00,742
I thought maybe
we could talk.

143
00:12:04,616 --> 00:12:08,324
Right now probably isn't
the best time.

144
00:12:08,357 --> 00:12:09,795
Nima?

145
00:12:11,364 --> 00:12:13,402
Geez. Nice.

146
00:12:14,371 --> 00:12:15,807
Nima!

147
00:12:37,116 --> 00:12:38,886
How do you know him?

148
00:12:38,919 --> 00:12:41,260
I don't.

149
00:12:41,293 --> 00:12:44,365
He showed up at my office today.

150
00:12:44,399 --> 00:12:46,971
-Did you invite him?
-No.

151
00:12:47,004 --> 00:12:49,442
He came by to ask
if I could help him talk to you.

152
00:12:49,476 --> 00:12:52,049
You just listened to
what he had to say?

153
00:12:52,082 --> 00:12:53,451
I mean, yeah.

154
00:12:56,357 --> 00:12:58,461
After everything
I've told you.

155
00:12:58,493 --> 00:13:01,534
Baby, all you ever said
was that he wasn't around.

156
00:13:01,568 --> 00:13:03,372
Any time his name comes up,
you get so angry,

157
00:13:03,405 --> 00:13:04,908
we can't even have
a conversation.

158
00:13:04,940 --> 00:13:06,944
What else
would I have to say?

159
00:13:06,978 --> 00:13:08,549
What did you expect me to do?

160
00:13:08,582 --> 00:13:10,421
Can you please take me home?

161
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:21,844
Are you mad at me?

162
00:13:21,876 --> 00:13:23,346
Just take me home.

163
00:13:27,421 --> 00:13:29,859
Mr. Babineaux.

164
00:13:36,273 --> 00:13:39,311
Well, y'all will never believe
who I saw yesterday.

165
00:13:39,345 --> 00:13:40,313
Who?

166
00:13:40,346 --> 00:13:42,117
My father.

167
00:13:42,150 --> 00:13:43,621
What?

168
00:13:43,655 --> 00:13:45,158
Yes.

169
00:13:45,190 --> 00:13:46,192
My father.

170
00:13:47,328 --> 00:13:48,899
Did you shake him?

171
00:13:48,932 --> 00:13:50,635
Did you toss hot grease
in his lap?

172
00:13:50,668 --> 00:13:52,372
Did you open-palm slap him?
I need details.

173
00:13:52,406 --> 00:13:54,444
Okay, Rochelle,
she would never do that.

174
00:13:54,477 --> 00:13:57,116
I would absolutely do
all of that, Tiffany.

175
00:13:58,350 --> 00:14:00,221
All right...

176
00:14:00,254 --> 00:14:02,359
But I didn't.

177
00:14:02,393 --> 00:14:04,229
I just left.

178
00:14:04,263 --> 00:14:06,435
Why was he there in the first
place?

179
00:14:06,468 --> 00:14:10,109
Spence claims that
he came by the office to see him

180
00:14:10,142 --> 00:14:12,682
and he asked for his help
in repairing our relationship.

181
00:14:12,715 --> 00:14:14,618
Cute.

182
00:14:14,652 --> 00:14:17,124
No.
Exactly.

183
00:14:17,157 --> 00:14:19,896
Nima, it's... it's time for
you to fix things with him.

184
00:14:19,928 --> 00:14:21,332
Sweetie, you're getting married.

185
00:14:21,366 --> 00:14:24,239
What does getting married
have to do with any of that?

186
00:14:24,271 --> 00:14:25,640
Because you're starting
a new life,

187
00:14:25,673 --> 00:14:27,912
and, typically, you want
all to be well in your world.

188
00:14:27,944 --> 00:14:30,015
All is well.

189
00:14:30,048 --> 00:14:32,356
You know, you just...
You don't understand.

190
00:14:32,389 --> 00:14:34,058
Okay, I see.

191
00:14:34,091 --> 00:14:35,929
It's because I have a dad,
right?

192
00:14:35,962 --> 00:14:37,165
Is that what it is?

193
00:14:37,198 --> 00:14:38,635
-Yes.
-Okay.

194
00:14:38,668 --> 00:14:40,371
You two, I...

195
00:14:40,404 --> 00:14:42,142
But Rochelle and I have
the better version of dads.

196
00:14:42,175 --> 00:14:43,243
Okay, what's that?

197
00:14:43,276 --> 00:14:44,412
They're called moms.

198
00:14:44,445 --> 00:14:46,082
Whatever.

199
00:14:46,116 --> 00:14:47,452
You know what?

200
00:14:58,206 --> 00:15:00,211
Boo!

201
00:15:02,783 --> 00:15:05,088
Othell Babineaux.

202
00:15:05,121 --> 00:15:07,125
Come here, man!
Benny Mitchell!

203
00:15:07,158 --> 00:15:09,264
How you doing, brother?
What's happening, cat daddy?

204
00:15:10,666 --> 00:15:13,240
Man, I ain't see you in what,
five years?

205
00:15:13,273 --> 00:15:15,310
We were in that Mexican jail.

206
00:15:15,342 --> 00:15:17,481
<i>You were in
that Mexican jail. Stop.</i>

207
00:15:17,514 --> 00:15:18,483
You playing anywhere?

208
00:15:18,515 --> 00:15:21,688
Well, you know, I'm...

209
00:15:21,722 --> 00:15:24,060
I fix cars.

210
00:15:24,093 --> 00:15:26,199
All that talent
and you changing oil?

211
00:15:26,232 --> 00:15:29,105
You got something here
for me, Benny?

212
00:15:29,638 --> 00:15:33,346
Man. I can't...

213
00:15:33,379 --> 00:15:38,023
Not after the missed practices,
showing up to gigs drunk.

214
00:15:38,056 --> 00:15:40,995
I mean, you punched a guy
in the audience, Othell.

215
00:15:41,028 --> 00:15:44,136
He was heckling me, man.

216
00:15:44,170 --> 00:15:46,174
He was clapping, o.

217
00:15:52,553 --> 00:15:54,692
Look...

218
00:15:58,063 --> 00:16:00,736
I need this, Benny.
I'm clean.

219
00:16:00,769 --> 00:16:02,572
How long?

220
00:16:02,606 --> 00:16:07,217
Two months, four days,
and seven and a half hours.

221
00:16:09,721 --> 00:16:11,759
O...

222
00:16:11,791 --> 00:16:14,733
I'm rooting for you
more than anybody.

223
00:16:14,766 --> 00:16:19,241
But you gotta prove you can be
a reliable musician, man.

224
00:16:19,274 --> 00:16:21,513
Yeah, we got another spot
for a piano player,

225
00:16:21,545 --> 00:16:23,383
but I can only
give it to someone

226
00:16:23,416 --> 00:16:24,719
who's gonna show up on time,

227
00:16:24,753 --> 00:16:27,258
come to rehearsal
without a bottle in his hand,

228
00:16:27,291 --> 00:16:29,329
and not throw up during a set,
brother.

229
00:16:29,362 --> 00:16:31,166
That happened once.

230
00:16:32,667 --> 00:16:34,506
It was on the bass player.

231
00:16:36,443 --> 00:16:38,447
Jimmy's still mad
about that?

232
00:16:38,480 --> 00:16:40,152
The suit was new.

233
00:16:43,692 --> 00:16:45,562
Look...

234
00:16:45,596 --> 00:16:48,368
If you can stay clean
another month,

235
00:16:48,402 --> 00:16:50,673
come back and see me.

236
00:16:50,706 --> 00:16:53,245
You know, I can look at you
and tell you ain't ready yet.

237
00:16:55,784 --> 00:16:58,422
Let me introduce you to my wife,
Martha, while you're here.

238
00:16:58,454 --> 00:17:00,126
Hey, baby.

239
00:17:12,416 --> 00:17:13,720
You have got to be
kidding me.

240
00:17:13,753 --> 00:17:14,822
You still stalking me?

241
00:17:14,855 --> 00:17:16,594
I want you and Nima
to come to

242
00:17:16,627 --> 00:17:20,601
my mama's 80th birthday party
in Savannah.

243
00:17:20,635 --> 00:17:22,705
Yeah. Well, good-bye,
Mr. Babineaux.

244
00:17:22,738 --> 00:17:25,611
Wait, wait, wait, Spence,
please, just give me a minute.

245
00:17:25,645 --> 00:17:28,317
You know, I made it
very clear to you before...

246
00:17:28,350 --> 00:17:29,285
I can't help you.

247
00:17:29,319 --> 00:17:33,261
And instead of sitting down
and figuring out

248
00:17:33,293 --> 00:17:34,831
what you could do
for your daughter,

249
00:17:34,863 --> 00:17:35,865
the first thing you do

250
00:17:35,899 --> 00:17:37,669
is ask her to do
something for you.

251
00:17:38,804 --> 00:17:41,276
You're everything
she always said you were.

252
00:17:41,310 --> 00:17:43,081
You're selfish.

253
00:17:44,182 --> 00:17:47,156
Then don't do this for me.
Do it for Nima.

254
00:17:47,724 --> 00:17:50,496
Come on, Spence,
you're a good man,

255
00:17:50,528 --> 00:17:53,535
but we both know
that deep down inside,

256
00:17:53,567 --> 00:17:56,608
Nima wants to fix this, too.

257
00:17:56,642 --> 00:17:59,815
You're a psychologist now?
No, no.

258
00:17:59,847 --> 00:18:05,159
But I let my issues
with my daddy ruin my marriage.

259
00:18:05,192 --> 00:18:08,466
Well, I'm not gonna let that
happen to ours.

260
00:18:08,499 --> 00:18:15,381
You can't control
how people respond to pain.

261
00:18:18,420 --> 00:18:21,526
I don't want to hurt her again.

262
00:18:21,558 --> 00:18:26,236
I just want a chance.

263
00:18:26,270 --> 00:18:28,141
Will you give me that?

264
00:18:32,915 --> 00:18:35,187
Are you gonna...

265
00:18:35,221 --> 00:18:36,659
Finish this?

266
00:18:49,751 --> 00:18:51,655
Baby, you want a drink?

267
00:18:51,687 --> 00:18:53,559
No, I'm fine.

268
00:19:16,672 --> 00:19:19,212
Babe...

269
00:19:19,246 --> 00:19:21,617
What's the story
with your dad?

270
00:19:23,821 --> 00:19:26,328
I need to know.

271
00:19:26,361 --> 00:19:29,834
You know what?
I don't like talking about him.

272
00:19:31,402 --> 00:19:33,440
Not even for me?

273
00:19:35,545 --> 00:19:38,552
Please?
Why this sudden interest?

274
00:19:38,584 --> 00:19:40,655
It's not sudden.

275
00:19:40,689 --> 00:19:42,727
I always wanted to know.

276
00:19:42,759 --> 00:19:45,266
Baby, that's in the past.

277
00:19:45,298 --> 00:19:47,904
That has nothing to do
with you and me.

278
00:19:47,938 --> 00:19:49,508
Mwah.

279
00:19:51,612 --> 00:19:54,718
Except that it has
absolutely everything

280
00:19:54,750 --> 00:19:56,356
to do with you and me.

281
00:19:58,425 --> 00:20:00,865
What does that mean?

282
00:20:00,897 --> 00:20:03,937
Baby, you don't trust me.

283
00:20:03,971 --> 00:20:05,740
Yes, I do.

284
00:20:05,773 --> 00:20:07,946
Not with your whole heart.

285
00:20:09,915 --> 00:20:11,787
You remember
when your grandfather

286
00:20:11,819 --> 00:20:14,558
was terminally ill?

287
00:20:14,591 --> 00:20:16,396
You didn't tell me
for two weeks,

288
00:20:16,429 --> 00:20:18,801
and you claimed it was
'cause I was busy at work,

289
00:20:18,835 --> 00:20:20,939
but I'm never too busy for you.

290
00:20:20,972 --> 00:20:24,614
You don't trust me
emotionally.

291
00:20:24,646 --> 00:20:26,985
Okay. Wait.

292
00:20:28,722 --> 00:20:30,961
Where is this coming from?

293
00:20:32,930 --> 00:20:35,001
Did you talk to him again?

294
00:20:35,034 --> 00:20:37,106
A little.

295
00:20:37,139 --> 00:20:38,842
You talked to him a little?

296
00:20:38,876 --> 00:20:41,382
Look, he came by my job today
when I was having lunch,

297
00:20:41,415 --> 00:20:45,657
and we talked.

298
00:20:45,689 --> 00:20:48,062
He's actually getting to you.
These are my feelings.

299
00:20:48,094 --> 00:20:49,731
They're not his.

300
00:20:49,764 --> 00:20:53,873
He's a conniving liar,
Spence.

301
00:20:53,907 --> 00:20:56,579
What did he say?

302
00:20:58,950 --> 00:21:00,420
Okay, I know this is

303
00:21:00,454 --> 00:21:02,758
out of nowhere
and it's last-minute,

304
00:21:02,791 --> 00:21:05,864
but he said he wants us
to go with him to Savannah

305
00:21:05,897 --> 00:21:09,540
for your grandmother's
80th birthday party.

306
00:21:09,573 --> 00:21:11,410
No!

307
00:21:11,442 --> 00:21:15,818
Do you know how selfish that is
for him to even ask me that?

308
00:21:16,820 --> 00:21:18,559
But I want to fix this.

309
00:21:20,962 --> 00:21:24,002
I want to fix this.
No, no, no, no.

310
00:21:24,036 --> 00:21:25,471
You're trying to fix me.

311
00:21:28,577 --> 00:21:29,748
Yeah.

312
00:21:32,553 --> 00:21:34,090
I'm gonna go.
I have to leave.

313
00:21:34,123 --> 00:21:35,526
-Babe.
-Okay? Good night.

314
00:21:35,558 --> 00:21:36,595
Baby?

315
00:21:41,136 --> 00:21:43,009
Where are my shoes?

316
00:21:47,450 --> 00:21:48,820
I live here.

317
00:21:50,724 --> 00:21:52,494
You go.

318
00:21:55,200 --> 00:21:56,636
Okay.

319
00:22:01,178 --> 00:22:02,815
I knew you lived here.

320
00:22:02,848 --> 00:22:05,020
I didn't know
what you were doing.

321
00:22:18,680 --> 00:22:20,385
Did you think about it?

322
00:22:25,161 --> 00:22:27,030
Yeah.

323
00:22:27,064 --> 00:22:28,702
And?

324
00:22:32,709 --> 00:22:34,914
Yeah, you know, I just...

325
00:22:34,947 --> 00:22:37,955
I don't... I don't want to.

326
00:22:38,989 --> 00:22:42,131
I have no desire to mend
my relationship with him.

327
00:22:43,631 --> 00:22:48,074
I know that sounds horrible,
but it's true.

328
00:22:48,108 --> 00:22:51,583
-Baby, he stalked me.
-I know.

329
00:22:51,615 --> 00:22:52,852
No, I want you
to think about that,

330
00:22:52,884 --> 00:22:54,221
almost to the point
of getting arrested.

331
00:22:54,255 --> 00:22:56,693
He stalked me for three weeks.

332
00:22:57,862 --> 00:23:02,238
Baby, he wanted me to lie
and tell you he was dying.

333
00:23:02,270 --> 00:23:05,009
He's crafty.

334
00:23:05,043 --> 00:23:06,648
No, baby, he's desperate.

335
00:23:11,257 --> 00:23:14,529
So maybe you could
look deep inside

336
00:23:14,563 --> 00:23:17,134
that beautiful heart
of yours

337
00:23:17,167 --> 00:23:20,141
and do this
because he needs it.

338
00:23:20,174 --> 00:23:21,779
Not because you do.

339
00:23:33,167 --> 00:23:34,570
Look at these.

340
00:23:37,676 --> 00:23:39,748
It's pretty.

341
00:23:39,782 --> 00:23:42,988
What you reading?
My favorite magazine.

342
00:23:46,896 --> 00:23:51,071
Are you really ready
to do this, Nima?

343
00:23:51,105 --> 00:23:54,312
I thought about it all night.

344
00:23:54,346 --> 00:23:59,891
But I've decided
I'm going to go to Savannah.

345
00:23:59,924 --> 00:24:02,062
It should earn me
double heaven points.

346
00:24:02,094 --> 00:24:04,098
-Heaven points?
-Yes.

347
00:24:04,131 --> 00:24:05,936
When you perform selfless acts,

348
00:24:05,968 --> 00:24:08,707
you get points
that help get you into heaven.

349
00:24:08,741 --> 00:24:10,245
Everyone knows that.

350
00:24:11,948 --> 00:24:14,219
Who's here?
I'm not expecting anybody.

351
00:24:14,253 --> 00:24:16,191
It's probably Charles.

352
00:24:16,224 --> 00:24:18,861
Charles? Charles who?

353
00:24:18,894 --> 00:24:21,033
He's just a friend of mine.

354
00:24:21,066 --> 00:24:23,672
Why is Charles at my door?

355
00:24:23,706 --> 00:24:25,610
He doesn't live far from here,

356
00:24:25,642 --> 00:24:27,780
and since I was coming
to see you...

357
00:24:27,814 --> 00:24:30,955
Well, it didn't make sense
for him to drive across town.

358
00:24:35,829 --> 00:24:40,974
You are looking
too good today.

359
00:24:45,349 --> 00:24:47,888
Good afternoon!

360
00:24:47,922 --> 00:24:51,296
You must be Nima,

361
00:24:51,328 --> 00:24:55,370
the beautiful daughter
of this beautiful woman.

362
00:24:55,404 --> 00:24:56,941
And you are?

363
00:24:56,973 --> 00:25:00,114
Charles, Covington,
Dr. Charles Covington.

364
00:25:00,146 --> 00:25:02,920
You work with my mom
at the hospital?

365
00:25:02,953 --> 00:25:05,157
Yes, yeah.
I'm a gynecologist.

366
00:25:05,191 --> 00:25:08,030
Of course you are.

367
00:25:09,732 --> 00:25:11,672
Where are you taking my mother?

368
00:25:11,704 --> 00:25:16,347
I've had the finest
restaurant downtown shut down

369
00:25:16,379 --> 00:25:18,953
just so we could dance alone.

370
00:25:21,626 --> 00:25:22,695
Romantic?

371
00:25:22,727 --> 00:25:24,363
Sounds like a waste of money.

372
00:25:24,397 --> 00:25:28,038
My dear,

373
00:25:28,070 --> 00:25:30,842
nothing is a waste of money
when you have enough.

374
00:25:32,246 --> 00:25:35,353
Yeah, you're like the p. Diddy
of reproduction.

375
00:25:35,387 --> 00:25:36,755
Diddy?

376
00:25:36,789 --> 00:25:39,194
Yeah, I like that!
No.

377
00:25:39,226 --> 00:25:43,803
Could you wait right here
one minute?

378
00:25:43,836 --> 00:25:46,142
Maybe.

379
00:25:47,244 --> 00:25:49,282
What is wrong with you?

380
00:25:49,314 --> 00:25:52,054
Mama, who is that crazy dude?

381
00:25:52,087 --> 00:25:53,992
He's my date.

382
00:25:58,199 --> 00:26:00,939
He is a bad decision.

383
00:26:03,711 --> 00:26:06,651
Yeah.

384
00:26:20,344 --> 00:26:22,218
I'll be right with you.

385
00:26:24,153 --> 00:26:25,656
Can I help you?

386
00:26:25,690 --> 00:26:28,930
Yeah, I want to use
one of the pianos.

387
00:26:28,962 --> 00:26:31,000
Yes.
Just sign in right here.

388
00:28:00,986 --> 00:28:02,824
Miss Babineaux.

389
00:28:02,856 --> 00:28:05,128
What are you doing here?
I thought it was your day off.

390
00:28:05,162 --> 00:28:06,865
It is.

391
00:28:06,898 --> 00:28:08,434
Did I leave
my music sheets here?

392
00:28:08,468 --> 00:28:11,842
-Yes, you did.
-I think.

393
00:28:11,875 --> 00:28:13,011
Thanks.

394
00:28:15,950 --> 00:28:19,157
Does that say
"Othell Babineaux?"

395
00:28:21,059 --> 00:28:22,498
Spence told me
to give you this

396
00:28:22,530 --> 00:28:24,167
whenever you found out.

397
00:28:24,201 --> 00:28:28,108
He paid for some gentleman
to use the extra piano

398
00:28:28,142 --> 00:28:30,113
to practice for some gig.

399
00:28:30,146 --> 00:28:31,950
Of course he did.

400
00:28:31,982 --> 00:28:35,124
He was only supposed
to be here on your day off.

401
00:30:42,418 --> 00:30:44,724
Hey! Mr. Babineaux.

402
00:30:44,756 --> 00:30:46,393
You know, I thought I said
I could come get you.

403
00:30:46,427 --> 00:30:48,497
Well, you know,
I wanted to show you this.

404
00:30:48,531 --> 00:30:51,404
Okay.
I guess that saves time.

405
00:30:55,545 --> 00:30:57,048
Othell?

406
00:30:58,719 --> 00:31:01,458
Well, you're looking better.

407
00:31:01,490 --> 00:31:03,728
You look
really nice yourself.

408
00:31:03,761 --> 00:31:05,799
It's really good
to see you again.

409
00:31:05,833 --> 00:31:07,537
I gotta go.

410
00:31:11,377 --> 00:31:12,446
Hi.

411
00:31:20,329 --> 00:31:21,999
Hello, Nima.

412
00:31:26,410 --> 00:31:28,113
It's gonna be a long trip.

413
00:31:34,625 --> 00:31:37,398
Finally getting on the road.

414
00:31:37,432 --> 00:31:41,207
Would anyone like
a Lancaster soft cream?

415
00:31:41,240 --> 00:31:43,810
You used to love caramel, Nima.

416
00:31:43,844 --> 00:31:46,083
I love these things.

417
00:31:48,288 --> 00:31:49,458
Yeah, I used to...

418
00:31:57,407 --> 00:31:59,343
Okay.

419
00:32:51,751 --> 00:32:53,254
Is he okay?

420
00:32:53,287 --> 00:32:56,294
-Mama! Mama!
-Hey!

421
00:32:56,326 --> 00:32:57,664
Mama!

422
00:33:05,512 --> 00:33:06,581
You made it!

423
00:33:06,615 --> 00:33:09,888
Go on back to the table,
Melinda.

424
00:33:09,922 --> 00:33:11,626
All these extra people.

425
00:33:11,658 --> 00:33:14,732
I'm so happy to see you!

426
00:33:16,568 --> 00:33:19,443
How are you?

427
00:33:19,475 --> 00:33:22,380
Well...
I'm doing fine, mama. I'm fine.

428
00:33:22,414 --> 00:33:24,385
You put on a few extra pounds
there, son.

429
00:33:24,417 --> 00:33:27,358
Yes, I have. I have.

430
00:33:27,390 --> 00:33:29,529
Well, who are these
young, attractive people

431
00:33:29,562 --> 00:33:30,464
you got with you?

432
00:33:30,497 --> 00:33:32,735
Mama...

433
00:33:32,769 --> 00:33:34,507
That's Nima...

434
00:33:34,540 --> 00:33:37,178
And her fiancé, Spence.

435
00:33:38,948 --> 00:33:42,523
My granddaughter.

436
00:33:42,556 --> 00:33:47,298
Baby! Honey!

437
00:33:50,305 --> 00:33:53,211
I been waiting my whole life
to meet you.

438
00:33:55,783 --> 00:33:58,523
Well...
Please, go on in.

439
00:33:58,555 --> 00:34:02,265
Y'all just in time for dinner.

440
00:34:10,381 --> 00:34:13,787
Look who's here!

441
00:34:16,593 --> 00:34:18,596
Hey, everybody.

442
00:34:18,630 --> 00:34:20,869
Y'all not gonna say hello?

443
00:34:20,902 --> 00:34:24,408
-Hello.
-Hey, bro.

444
00:34:24,442 --> 00:34:27,582
Well, o brought his daughter,
Nima.

445
00:34:27,614 --> 00:34:29,387
And her fiancé, Spence.

446
00:34:33,460 --> 00:34:36,500
Well, this is your uncle James
and his wife, Denise.

447
00:34:36,534 --> 00:34:39,374
People used to always say
that James and Othell

448
00:34:39,406 --> 00:34:40,676
looked the most alike.

449
00:34:40,709 --> 00:34:43,816
This is your uncle Joseph
and his wife, Nancy.

450
00:34:43,848 --> 00:34:46,453
Joseph is
the quiet one of the bunch.

451
00:34:46,486 --> 00:34:49,494
And this is my second oldest,
Melinda.

452
00:34:49,527 --> 00:34:51,799
And my youngest, Marvin.

453
00:34:51,831 --> 00:34:54,538
His family couldn't make it.

454
00:34:57,277 --> 00:34:59,549
Well, y'all go on and sit down.

455
00:34:59,582 --> 00:35:01,687
His family never makes it.

456
00:35:05,961 --> 00:35:07,964
Well, y'all know

457
00:35:07,997 --> 00:35:12,040
that I'm not much for words.
Right, mama.

458
00:35:12,074 --> 00:35:15,348
But I just wanted to say
thank you, all of you,

459
00:35:15,380 --> 00:35:17,985
for coming out to my
80th birthday party.

460
00:35:18,018 --> 00:35:21,860
I want to thank my second-eldest
Melinda.

461
00:35:21,894 --> 00:35:25,267
She did a beautiful job
with this party.

462
00:35:25,300 --> 00:35:26,770
Thank you.

463
00:35:26,803 --> 00:35:30,312
And I want to thank
James and Joseph for the cake

464
00:35:30,346 --> 00:35:33,786
and the lovely portrait
for the living room.

465
00:35:33,819 --> 00:35:36,592
But I am most excited

466
00:35:36,625 --> 00:35:41,468
that Othell
and my granddaughter Nima

467
00:35:41,501 --> 00:35:46,011
are sitting at this table
together.

468
00:35:46,043 --> 00:35:51,422
Nima and Spence,
I'm so glad to have you here.

469
00:35:51,455 --> 00:35:53,593
Let's eat!
Yes!

470
00:35:55,062 --> 00:35:58,402
Mama, did James tell you
about his good news?

471
00:35:58,435 --> 00:36:00,541
No, baby, what happened?

472
00:36:00,574 --> 00:36:04,448
Well, mama, I was offered
a position at hennig and white.

473
00:36:04,481 --> 00:36:06,987
My baby brother now works for

474
00:36:07,019 --> 00:36:10,562
<i>the largest law firm
in the country.</i>

475
00:36:10,595 --> 00:36:14,569
Soon to be walking in
his father's footsteps,

476
00:36:14,602 --> 00:36:16,004
becoming a judge.

477
00:36:16,037 --> 00:36:18,610
Well, congratulations, baby.

478
00:36:18,644 --> 00:36:20,582
Joseph has good news, too.

479
00:36:20,615 --> 00:36:21,784
Go ahead, Joseph.

480
00:36:21,817 --> 00:36:23,488
Go on, tell her.

481
00:36:23,521 --> 00:36:25,659
I passed the bar.

482
00:36:27,061 --> 00:36:29,433
Congratulations,
baby brother.

483
00:36:29,465 --> 00:36:31,338
Now, let's see.

484
00:36:31,370 --> 00:36:34,912
Dad, god rest his soul,
was an esteemed judge.

485
00:36:34,944 --> 00:36:37,015
Mama, a retired nurse.

486
00:36:37,048 --> 00:36:38,818
I'm a doctor.

487
00:36:38,852 --> 00:36:40,856
We have two lawyers.

488
00:36:40,888 --> 00:36:45,500
And, Marvin,
he's a top financial advisor.

489
00:36:45,532 --> 00:36:47,603
Yes.

490
00:36:47,636 --> 00:36:49,841
Good.

491
00:36:49,875 --> 00:36:51,613
Othell, what do you do?

492
00:36:51,646 --> 00:36:53,617
Your brother's fine, Melinda.

493
00:36:53,649 --> 00:36:55,387
Mama, I know he's fine.

494
00:36:55,419 --> 00:36:56,756
It's just been such a long time.

495
00:36:56,789 --> 00:36:58,025
I haven't seen him in years.

496
00:36:58,059 --> 00:37:00,664
I don't remember what he does.

497
00:37:03,536 --> 00:37:06,609
I have a...

498
00:37:06,643 --> 00:37:08,414
A car repair shop.

499
00:37:08,446 --> 00:37:10,584
You have, or you had?

500
00:37:10,618 --> 00:37:12,689
-Melinda!
-No, mama.

501
00:37:12,722 --> 00:37:16,831
This is a special day
for family.

502
00:37:16,863 --> 00:37:19,336
Not for a man
who was too drunk

503
00:37:19,369 --> 00:37:20,939
to attend
his own father's funeral.

504
00:37:20,972 --> 00:37:23,044
Would you shut up?

505
00:37:23,076 --> 00:37:25,515
How could you ruin
my birthday party

506
00:37:25,547 --> 00:37:27,719
with this your stupid,
stuck-up ways?

507
00:37:27,754 --> 00:37:30,426
-I'm sorry, mama. I'm sorry.
-Shut up!

508
00:37:32,863 --> 00:37:34,635
Just shut up.

509
00:37:45,489 --> 00:37:48,596
Hey, what do you say
we take a walk,

510
00:37:48,629 --> 00:37:50,133
check out the pond?

511
00:37:50,165 --> 00:37:52,637
Now, I haven't seen the pond
in years.

512
00:37:52,672 --> 00:37:55,510
Sure.
It's still there.

513
00:37:55,543 --> 00:37:57,614
All right, I'll get something
out of the car.

514
00:37:57,648 --> 00:37:59,653
I'll catch up with you.
All right.

515
00:38:08,236 --> 00:38:11,209
-A lot of memories down here.
-Yeah, yeah.

516
00:38:14,650 --> 00:38:16,387
Yeah, there is.

517
00:38:17,857 --> 00:38:21,063
What you been up to, man?

518
00:38:21,096 --> 00:38:22,834
I tried to...

519
00:38:22,867 --> 00:38:24,603
I tried to call you
a couple of times.

520
00:38:24,637 --> 00:38:26,173
Your number keeps changing.

521
00:38:26,207 --> 00:38:28,746
Well, I ain't been doing
nothing, man.

522
00:38:30,515 --> 00:38:33,989
Did you ever get your...
Your gig back at the club?

523
00:38:34,022 --> 00:38:36,828
No.

524
00:38:36,862 --> 00:38:40,637
I got a promotion on Friday.

525
00:38:41,938 --> 00:38:44,813
$10,000 raise.

526
00:38:46,648 --> 00:38:47,885
My wife...

527
00:38:47,919 --> 00:38:51,859
She's pregnant
with our third child.

528
00:38:51,892 --> 00:38:56,636
