00:56:51,883 --> 00:56:56,760
Did she tell you
that she slapped Melinda?

800
00:56:56,793 --> 00:56:59,298
Yes.

801
00:56:59,332 --> 00:57:01,136
How is Melinda?

802
00:57:01,169 --> 00:57:03,808
She misses you.

803
00:57:03,841 --> 00:57:05,711
Still no drinking?

804
00:57:05,745 --> 00:57:08,986
This is water.

805
00:57:09,018 --> 00:57:11,858
Almost three months.

806
00:57:11,891 --> 00:57:16,601
Well, actually, it's been
two months, 12 days,

807
00:57:16,633 --> 00:57:19,674
and three and a half hours.

808
00:57:19,707 --> 00:57:22,680
You cannot mess this up.

809
00:57:23,883 --> 00:57:28,125
You've never even given me
a chance to mess up.

810
00:57:30,329 --> 00:57:32,869
What about the club?

811
00:57:35,306 --> 00:57:40,151
I went to get my gig back
and froze up.

812
00:57:42,455 --> 00:57:44,960
What did you want to show me?

813
00:57:44,993 --> 00:57:48,232
I know it's Nima's birthday
Tuesday.

814
00:57:48,265 --> 00:57:49,870
Yeah?

815
00:57:52,007 --> 00:57:53,677
What is this?

816
00:57:53,710 --> 00:57:56,415
I want to do
something special.

817
00:57:56,449 --> 00:57:59,188
You want to take her
to the bistro?

818
00:57:59,221 --> 00:58:00,959
You think she'll go?

819
00:58:00,992 --> 00:58:06,803
I'll see what I can do.

820
00:58:40,974 --> 00:58:43,346
Nima?

821
00:58:43,380 --> 00:58:46,954
Nima, I thought we were
meeting at the restaurant.

822
00:58:54,069 --> 00:58:56,908
You remind me
so much of your mother.

823
00:59:01,384 --> 00:59:04,291
I know you want to know
why I wasn't there

824
00:59:04,324 --> 00:59:06,927
and why it seems
like I didn't try,

825
00:59:06,960 --> 00:59:08,732
but...

826
00:59:10,101 --> 00:59:12,040
I don't have those answers.

827
00:59:14,944 --> 00:59:18,886
I ask myself
the same thing every day.

828
00:59:21,224 --> 00:59:23,163
I always...

829
00:59:24,364 --> 00:59:26,835
thought you
deserved a father.

830
00:59:28,773 --> 00:59:30,978
Just one much better than me.

831
00:59:33,216 --> 00:59:35,187
I know this...

832
00:59:35,220 --> 00:59:37,024
Won't be worth
much to you,

833
00:59:37,057 --> 00:59:41,533
but you're
the kind of daughter

834
00:59:41,565 --> 00:59:44,505
a father
would dream of having.

835
00:59:48,147 --> 00:59:50,817
Smart...

836
00:59:50,851 --> 00:59:52,824
Talented.

837
01:00:08,420 --> 01:00:09,824
Just...

838
01:00:11,896 --> 01:00:13,466
Just some things...

839
01:00:14,601 --> 01:00:16,539
I needed you to know.

840
01:00:35,577 --> 01:00:38,952
Have a seat.

841
01:00:38,985 --> 01:00:41,122
What's up, man?

842
01:00:41,155 --> 01:00:42,994
Well, I called you down here
because...

843
01:00:43,026 --> 01:00:45,131
I thought about it
a lot.

844
01:00:46,267 --> 01:00:47,970
I talked to Jax.

845
01:00:48,002 --> 01:00:51,910
I let Jax know that
you're working on being clean,

846
01:00:51,944 --> 01:00:53,582
and you're succeeding.

847
01:00:53,614 --> 01:00:56,053
So I got you
another audition tomorrow.

848
01:00:57,389 --> 01:01:00,395
Come on, man.
We go way back.

849
01:01:00,427 --> 01:01:02,599
We done played
hundreds of gigs together.

850
01:01:02,633 --> 01:01:04,670
It's just
a walk down memory Lane,

851
01:01:04,705 --> 01:01:07,043
except you're clean
this time.

852
01:01:10,281 --> 01:01:11,385
Well...

853
01:01:13,255 --> 01:01:16,895
I... I am clean, you know,
I'm clean, I'm clean.

854
01:01:16,929 --> 01:01:20,904
No shakes, no nothing, but...

855
01:01:20,936 --> 01:01:23,309
Ain't no buts, brother.

856
01:01:23,343 --> 01:01:25,447
Tell me you got it.

857
01:01:27,351 --> 01:01:30,090
-Tomorrow?
-Tomorrow, 10:00.

858
01:01:33,998 --> 01:01:37,071
All right, I'll be ready.

859
01:01:37,105 --> 01:01:39,109
Why can't they sit
next to each other?

860
01:01:39,141 --> 01:01:41,980
Trust me, they shouldn't.

861
01:01:42,013 --> 01:01:44,319
Has your boss rsvp'd yet?

862
01:01:44,353 --> 01:01:47,525
Yeah, they're right here.

863
01:01:47,559 --> 01:01:50,131
They want fish and steak.

864
01:01:50,164 --> 01:01:52,002
Good job!

865
01:01:58,580 --> 01:02:00,318
-We're done?
-We're done.

866
01:02:00,352 --> 01:02:02,522
-All done?
-All done!

867
01:02:04,427 --> 01:02:05,998
Finally!

868
01:02:09,103 --> 01:02:10,205
Excited?

869
01:02:11,608 --> 01:02:14,315
Did you finish the music
for your concert?

870
01:02:14,348 --> 01:02:16,019
Yes.

871
01:02:17,421 --> 01:02:19,191
I did.

872
01:02:19,223 --> 01:02:21,194
And you're inviting your dad?

873
01:02:22,263 --> 01:02:24,102
No.

874
01:02:24,134 --> 01:02:26,639
I'm not inviting him.

875
01:02:28,643 --> 01:02:30,715
Okay.

876
01:02:30,748 --> 01:02:33,119
Don't even think about
doing that.

877
01:02:33,152 --> 01:02:34,422
What? What did I do?

878
01:02:34,455 --> 01:02:37,229
I know you.
Just don't.

879
01:02:37,261 --> 01:02:40,468
I'm not gonna
invite your dad.

880
01:02:40,501 --> 01:02:43,574
No, I mean it.

881
01:03:04,652 --> 01:03:05,687
Benny?

882
01:03:05,719 --> 01:03:07,625
It's Spence.

883
01:03:07,658 --> 01:03:09,495
Right, yeah.
It's good to hear.

884
01:03:09,527 --> 01:03:11,632
Hey, listen,

885
01:03:11,665 --> 01:03:13,268
Nima's doing a small performance
for friends and family.

886
01:03:13,301 --> 01:03:15,339
It would mean a lot
if you were there,

887
01:03:15,372 --> 01:03:17,110
but I need you
to wear a suit.

888
01:03:18,546 --> 01:03:22,555
Yeah.
Yeah, between you and me.

889
01:03:22,588 --> 01:03:23,657
All right.

890
01:03:26,663 --> 01:03:28,301
You ready?

891
01:03:28,334 --> 01:03:31,440
Time to shine, baby.
All right.

892
01:03:31,473 --> 01:03:32,709
Thank you, man.

893
01:03:32,741 --> 01:03:34,312
Don't thank him yet.

894
01:04:12,924 --> 01:04:15,129
Looks like we found
our new piano player.

895
01:04:15,162 --> 01:04:16,432
That's right!

896
01:04:16,465 --> 01:04:18,203
Congrats, baby boy,
you're back!

897
01:04:18,235 --> 01:04:20,074
But they didn't do
a good job.

898
01:04:20,107 --> 01:04:21,610
No, I know.

899
01:04:21,643 --> 01:04:23,112
-Hey, babe.
-Hey, ladies.

900
01:04:23,145 --> 01:04:24,648
Hey, how are you?

901
01:04:24,681 --> 01:04:25,818
That's my seat.

902
01:04:25,852 --> 01:04:27,254
You were late.

903
01:04:27,289 --> 01:04:28,591
Sit right here, hon.

904
01:04:28,624 --> 01:04:30,729
Snooze you lose, I'm sorry.

905
01:04:30,762 --> 01:04:33,300
I get the nice view for once.

906
01:04:33,332 --> 01:04:35,370
So...

907
01:04:35,403 --> 01:04:38,610
She was telling me that
she likes her father again.

908
01:04:38,643 --> 01:04:40,783
Okay, no, she's not saying
that she likes her father,

909
01:04:40,815 --> 01:04:42,585
she's saying
that she's trying.

910
01:04:42,618 --> 01:04:44,389
Okay, don't do that.

911
01:04:44,422 --> 01:04:45,892
She needs to reconcile with him.

912
01:04:45,925 --> 01:04:48,198
This is a good, mature decision.

913
01:04:48,231 --> 01:04:49,266
-No.
-Yes.

914
01:04:49,300 --> 01:04:50,570
He had his chance.

915
01:04:50,602 --> 01:04:52,506
Why does he get
the best part of her now?

916
01:04:52,539 --> 01:04:53,842
He missed the teenage attitude,

917
01:04:53,876 --> 01:04:55,613
and the impoverished
college years.

918
01:04:55,646 --> 01:04:57,852
She's all
shiny and grown-up now.

919
01:04:57,884 --> 01:04:59,589
All right,
maybe you didn't hear that,

920
01:04:59,622 --> 01:05:01,290
but Nima told us
his whole life story.

921
01:05:01,324 --> 01:05:02,427
The man is damaged.

922
01:05:02,460 --> 01:05:03,496
That accounts for his absence.

923
01:05:03,529 --> 01:05:05,233
Come on, now, he's trying.

924
01:05:05,265 --> 01:05:06,903
I think she's setting
herself up to get hurt again.

925
01:05:06,936 --> 01:05:08,706
Okay, you are such
a hypocrite.

926
01:05:08,740 --> 01:05:11,212
You spoke to your father,
remember?

927
01:05:11,244 --> 01:05:12,882
Yeah. Because he was dying.

928
01:05:12,914 --> 01:05:15,454
Othell still has some time
to suffer.

929
01:05:15,487 --> 01:05:16,589
Okay, the point is, okay,

930
01:05:16,624 --> 01:05:18,727
she's making some huge
emotional strides in her life,

931
01:05:18,761 --> 01:05:20,899
and we need to be there for her,
okay?

932
01:05:20,931 --> 01:05:22,502
Well, is he coming to
the wedding?

933
01:05:26,844 --> 01:05:28,614
I'm permitted to speak?

934
01:05:28,648 --> 01:05:29,684
Yeah.

935
01:05:29,717 --> 01:05:32,189
No, he's not.

936
01:05:32,222 --> 01:05:34,226
It would be weird.
Okay.

937
01:05:34,259 --> 01:05:35,695
Fine by me.

938
01:05:35,728 --> 01:05:38,368
Now, can we talk about
something less depressing?

939
01:05:38,401 --> 01:05:41,575
-Like boys?
-No, I said less depressing.

940
01:05:41,607 --> 01:05:42,910
Okay.

941
01:05:57,339 --> 01:05:58,878
Come on, man.

942
01:05:58,910 --> 01:06:00,312
I...

943
01:06:00,345 --> 01:06:03,219
I thought I had a suit
in here.

944
01:06:03,718 --> 01:06:06,758
-Thank you.
-Hey. Sweetie, how are you?

945
01:06:11,902 --> 01:06:14,676
-Well, hello.
-Hey.

946
01:06:14,708 --> 01:06:15,944
I can't wait to hear
your music.

947
01:06:15,978 --> 01:06:18,718
I can't wait, either.

948
01:06:21,488 --> 01:06:23,894
Before you get started,
I got something to tell you.

949
01:06:23,927 --> 01:06:25,831
What?

950
01:06:25,865 --> 01:06:28,304
I...

951
01:06:28,337 --> 01:06:30,475
I invited your father.

952
01:06:34,783 --> 01:06:37,757
He said he was coming.

953
01:06:37,789 --> 01:06:40,429
Okay.

954
01:06:40,463 --> 01:06:42,968
I guess that's okay.
Yeah?

955
01:06:43,001 --> 01:06:45,439
Okay.

956
01:06:48,379 --> 01:06:49,783
You'll do great.

957
01:06:55,359 --> 01:06:57,297
Shoot!

958
01:07:10,424 --> 01:07:13,832
I want to thank you all
for coming.

959
01:07:15,399 --> 01:07:17,404
It means so much.

960
01:08:17,762 --> 01:08:19,601
Sorry.
I'm sorry.

961
01:08:21,536 --> 01:08:22,906
I'm sorry!

962
01:08:22,939 --> 01:08:25,378
I'm sorry.

963
01:08:25,411 --> 01:08:28,049
It's okay.

964
01:08:29,554 --> 01:08:31,725
Could everyone please
give us a minute?

965
01:08:42,446 --> 01:08:44,417
Nima, listen, I...

966
01:08:44,450 --> 01:08:46,754
Shut up.

967
01:08:46,788 --> 01:08:48,392
Just shut up!

968
01:08:48,424 --> 01:08:52,066
I'm tired of talking about
what you don't do.

969
01:08:52,099 --> 01:08:54,873
Let's talk about what you did.

970
01:08:57,577 --> 01:09:02,656
I'm a mess because of you.

971
01:09:02,688 --> 01:09:05,059
I can't love my fiancé
the way I want to

972
01:09:05,093 --> 01:09:08,133
because of you.

973
01:09:08,166 --> 01:09:13,411
I am curt, I'm mean,
and I'm dissatisfied with life

974
01:09:13,443 --> 01:09:15,481
<i>because of you.</i>

975
01:09:16,850 --> 01:09:22,931
I so desperately wanted
to be a daddy's girl.

976
01:09:22,963 --> 01:09:28,775
I clung to my mother's father
for dear life.

977
01:09:28,809 --> 01:09:33,585
And when he died,
so did a piece of me.

978
01:09:33,619 --> 01:09:36,825
I've put the burden on my mother

979
01:09:36,859 --> 01:09:40,901
to be my everything
because of you,

980
01:09:40,933 --> 01:09:42,838
and you know what kills me?

981
01:09:42,870 --> 01:09:45,677
I keep waiting
for Spence to leave.

982
01:09:48,683 --> 01:09:51,724
Because I can't possibly
wrap my mind around

983
01:09:51,756 --> 01:09:54,161
why he would stay!

984
01:09:54,763 --> 01:09:57,702
Because you didn't!

985
01:09:57,734 --> 01:10:01,042
You're my dad!

986
01:10:01,075 --> 01:10:04,682
Dads are supposed to be there.

987
01:10:04,716 --> 01:10:06,753
Because I'm yours!

988
01:10:15,504 --> 01:10:19,614
<i>Don't ever contact me again!</i>

989
01:10:23,822 --> 01:10:27,730
Jeannette...

990
01:10:27,763 --> 01:10:30,835
You're never going to tell her,
are you?

991
01:10:41,259 --> 01:10:42,962
I'm okay.

992
01:10:45,099 --> 01:10:47,505
I just had to get that out.

993
01:10:50,743 --> 01:10:53,316
You sure?

994
01:10:53,350 --> 01:10:55,754
I don't want to
talk about it.

995
01:10:55,788 --> 01:10:58,226
But aren't you, like, at
least a little concerned

996
01:10:58,260 --> 01:11:00,897
about why he didn't show up?

997
01:11:00,931 --> 01:11:04,639
Are you serious?

998
01:11:04,673 --> 01:11:07,312
Why don't you ever take my side?

999
01:11:07,344 --> 01:11:09,883
It's not about taking sides.
I'm not taking anybody's side.

1000
01:11:09,917 --> 01:11:12,656
It's just that we were making
some really good strides,

1001
01:11:12,689 --> 01:11:13,893
and all of a...
"We"?

1002
01:11:13,925 --> 01:11:16,764
The last time I checked,

1003
01:11:16,798 --> 01:11:19,670
<i>I was the one who was given
the ultimatum</i>

1004
01:11:19,704 --> 01:11:23,846
about getting to know my dad
or losing my fiancé.

1005
01:11:23,880 --> 01:11:25,116
I never said that.

1006
01:11:25,148 --> 01:11:26,684
I didn't...
I never said those words.

1007
01:11:26,717 --> 01:11:29,991
Spence, look,
I grew up without a father.

1008
01:11:30,023 --> 01:11:34,668
And surprise, surprise,
it has affected me negatively.

1009
01:11:34,702 --> 01:11:37,341
Do you know
how many books I've read?

1010
01:11:37,373 --> 01:11:40,045
How many articles
I have combed through

1011
01:11:40,078 --> 01:11:41,347
trying to be better?

1012
01:11:41,381 --> 01:11:43,186
I have made peace
with the fact

1013
01:11:43,218 --> 01:11:45,725
that I am not gonna be the girl
who has a dad!

1014
01:11:45,757 --> 01:11:47,227
You haven't made peace.

1015
01:11:47,261 --> 01:11:50,033
You're the opposite of peace.
You make war, Nima.

1016
01:11:50,066 --> 01:11:54,776
You make war with me every day,
you make war with yourself.

1017
01:11:54,808 --> 01:11:56,580
You're not at peace.

1018
01:11:57,281 --> 01:11:59,719
Spence, I am broken.

1019
01:12:02,693 --> 01:12:05,700
I didn't ask for you
to make me whole.

1020
01:12:07,367 --> 01:12:09,941
I just want you to love
the pieces.

1021
01:12:12,445 --> 01:12:13,983
You think I don't?

1022
01:12:17,456 --> 01:12:19,761
But you... you can fix
those pieces.

1023
01:12:19,793 --> 01:12:21,764
You could fix them
if you chose to.

1024
01:12:24,303 --> 01:12:27,711
I don't even know why
we're getting married.

1025
01:12:28,177 --> 01:12:30,649
What did you say?

1026
01:12:30,682 --> 01:12:33,056
-What did you say?
-You heard what I said.

1027
01:12:33,088 --> 01:12:36,328
I don't think
we should be getting married.

1028
01:12:36,361 --> 01:12:38,933
I mean, look at us!

1029
01:12:38,967 --> 01:12:40,236
You don't want
to get married?

1030
01:12:40,268 --> 01:12:41,739
No, I don't want
to get married.

1031
01:12:41,772 --> 01:12:43,177
You don't want
to get married to me?

1032
01:12:43,210 --> 01:12:45,247
Look at us! I don't want
to get married like this.

1033
01:12:45,280 --> 01:12:47,884
-You don't even like me.
-Fine, fine!

1034
01:12:47,918 --> 01:12:50,090
Fine. Fine.

1035
01:12:50,124 --> 01:12:52,428
Can you please just stop
the car so I can get out?

1036
01:12:52,460 --> 01:12:53,864
No, I'm not stopping, no.

1037
01:12:53,898 --> 01:12:55,868
No, you're not gonna
run away from me.

1038
01:12:55,902 --> 01:12:59,109
Stop the car
so I can get out!

1039
01:12:59,141 --> 01:13:00,879
Can you stop the car now?

1040
01:13:22,356 --> 01:13:24,629
Hey, what can I get for you?

1041
01:13:31,843 --> 01:13:33,915
I'll be back with you in a sec.

1042
01:13:49,345 --> 01:13:51,449
What in the world
are you doing

1043
01:13:51,483 --> 01:13:52,953
in a place like this?

1044
01:14:02,137 --> 01:14:03,841
I should knock you out,

1045
01:14:03,874 --> 01:14:05,780
right here in this bar, man.

1046
01:14:07,950 --> 01:14:12,025
You... You ruined
my relationship...

1047
01:14:12,057 --> 01:14:15,031
Just like you ruined yours.

1048
01:14:15,064 --> 01:14:17,803
I missed
the performance tonight

1049
01:14:17,836 --> 01:14:20,341
because
if she does forgive me,

1050
01:14:20,375 --> 01:14:23,148
I ain't got nothing
to give her.

1051
01:14:23,180 --> 01:14:26,054
I don't care anymore!

1052
01:14:26,087 --> 01:14:27,893
Everything all right?

1053
01:14:31,465 --> 01:14:32,902
So what you having, man?

1054
01:14:32,934 --> 01:14:34,739
Nothing.

1055
01:14:35,908 --> 01:14:38,381
He's an alcoholic.

1056
01:14:58,321 --> 01:14:59,557
Hey, get off me!

1057
01:14:59,589 --> 01:15:02,095
You're not going anywhere
like this!

1058
01:15:02,129 --> 01:15:03,565
You're not driving anywhere
like this.

1059
01:15:03,598 --> 01:15:05,136
I said... I said get off me!

1060
01:15:05,169 --> 01:15:08,041
You're not driving anywhere
like this.

1061
01:15:08,073 --> 01:15:10,077
Now, give me them keys.

1062
01:15:10,111 --> 01:15:11,948
Give me the keys!

1063
01:15:15,189 --> 01:15:18,963
I'm taking you home,
and you're gonna sober up...

1064
01:15:20,934 --> 01:15:24,976
and go apologize
to your future wife.

1065
01:15:26,878 --> 01:15:29,251
Now, you come on.

1066
01:15:29,284 --> 01:15:30,954
Come on, son.

1067
01:15:32,290 --> 01:15:33,761
Come on.

1068
01:16:00,314 --> 01:16:01,984
Rough night?

1069
01:16:07,898 --> 01:16:08,967
Rum.

1070
01:16:10,401 --> 01:16:12,106
I think I had too much rum.

1071
01:16:14,276 --> 01:16:15,613
It's not funny.

1072
01:16:22,494 --> 01:16:23,996
Baby, I'm sorry.

1073
01:16:24,030 --> 01:16:26,603
I'm sorry.

1074
01:16:26,635 --> 01:16:29,008
Spence, I don't want to be
in a marriage

1075
01:16:29,040 --> 01:16:31,077
where you won't let me
be my true self.

1076
01:16:31,111 --> 01:16:33,884
I know, me, too.

1077
01:16:33,916 --> 01:16:36,254
And giving you my everything...
It isn't hard,

1078
01:16:36,288 --> 01:16:38,294
but it's scary.

1079
01:16:40,264 --> 01:16:46,276
It takes courage for you
to love me the way you love me,

1080
01:16:46,309 --> 01:16:50,085
and I always
want to reciprocate that.

1081
01:16:50,118 --> 01:16:52,155
You do, and I'm sorry if I...

1082
01:16:55,159 --> 01:16:57,566
if I don't make
you feel like that.

1083
01:16:57,600 --> 01:16:59,437
I'm so happy.

1084
01:16:59,471 --> 01:17:01,341
You have to know that.

1085
01:17:01,373 --> 01:17:04,079
But you have to let me...

1086
01:17:04,113 --> 01:17:06,017
Let me do things on my own time.

1087
01:17:06,049 --> 01:17:07,221
Okay.

1088
01:17:09,657 --> 01:17:12,030
Baby, do you still
want to marry me?

1089
01:17:12,062 --> 01:17:13,933
Yes.

1090
01:17:26,925 --> 01:17:30,466
How much rum did you have?

1091
01:17:30,500 --> 01:17:31,703
A lot.

1092
01:17:44,997 --> 01:17:48,973
This is so nice!

1093
01:17:49,005 --> 01:17:51,645
It actually is, mama.

1094
01:17:51,677 --> 01:17:54,349
There is no way
that I would ever

1095
01:17:54,383 --> 01:17:56,989
come to my grandbaby's
wedding without you.

1096
01:17:57,657 --> 01:17:59,995
You need to be here.

1097
01:18:09,514 --> 01:18:11,551
Let me look at you!

1098
01:18:11,585 --> 01:18:14,591
Look at you!
You haven't aged a day!

1099
01:18:14,625 --> 01:18:16,094
Well, neither have you.

1100
01:18:16,126 --> 01:18:17,630
Look at you!

1101
01:18:17,663 --> 01:18:20,471
My goodness.

1102
01:18:26,448 --> 01:18:28,186
I'm just here because...

1103
01:18:28,220 --> 01:18:30,993
You are her father.

1104
01:18:33,329 --> 01:18:37,672
Jeannette and I,
we had a long talk last night.

1105
01:18:39,242 --> 01:18:42,048
She's gonna make it right.

1106
01:18:42,080 --> 01:18:43,418
Today.

1107
01:18:45,087 --> 01:18:46,223
I am.

1108
01:19:02,724 --> 01:19:03,993
Hi, baby.

1109
01:19:05,630 --> 01:19:07,199
Hi, mama.

1110
01:19:07,233 --> 01:19:09,037
Come here, sweetheart.

1111
01:19:09,069 --> 01:19:11,208
I want to talk to you
for a minute.

1112
01:19:16,185 --> 01:19:17,756
What's wrong?

1113
01:19:21,428 --> 01:19:23,433
This is so hard for me to say.

1114
01:19:26,638 --> 01:19:29,579
I've been lying to you
about your father.

1115
01:19:31,317 --> 01:19:34,256
What do you mean?

1116
01:19:34,289 --> 01:19:37,563
I know I've made it seem like
he never tried to...

1117
01:19:37,595 --> 01:19:39,701
To see you or call you

1118
01:19:39,733 --> 01:19:43,407
or send you cards
on your birthday.

1119
01:19:43,440 --> 01:19:46,346
But he did.

1120
01:19:46,380 --> 01:19:48,752
He sent you letters for years...

1121
01:19:50,655 --> 01:19:52,626
along with...

1122
01:19:52,659 --> 01:19:55,499
Little gifts on your birthday.

1123
01:20:03,115 --> 01:20:08,092
And he sent you money,
whatever he had at the time.

1124
01:20:12,500 --> 01:20:13,737
Mama, why would you
hide this from me?

1125
01:20:13,771 --> 01:20:19,447
I loved your father so much,
Nima.

1126
01:20:19,481 --> 01:20:22,122
And when he left,
he took my heart with him.

1127
01:20:22,155 --> 01:20:24,460
I was just so mad.

1128
01:20:25,928 --> 01:20:27,532
All I wanted was him.

1129
01:20:27,564 --> 01:20:30,271
I didn't care about the money
or any of that.

1130
01:20:30,305 --> 01:20:32,710
I just wanted him,
but he never got it.

1131
01:20:32,743 --> 01:20:35,415
So when he left,
I just decided

1132
01:20:35,448 --> 01:20:39,389
that I would make him feel
the same pain that I felt

1133
01:20:39,421 --> 01:20:40,893
by keeping you away.

1134
01:20:50,445 --> 01:20:52,450
You tell me this
on my wedding day?

1135
01:20:52,484 --> 01:20:54,221
I'm so sorry, sweetheart.

1136
01:20:54,253 --> 01:20:56,792
I just want you
to have a fresh start.

1137
01:21:06,979 --> 01:21:08,616
Thank you.

1138
01:21:11,956 --> 01:21:13,426
You know, one day,
you just wake up

1139
01:21:13,460 --> 01:21:15,598
and you decide
not to be mad anymore?

1140
01:21:18,670 --> 01:21:20,609
Today is that day.

1141
01:21:22,244 --> 01:21:24,583
Sweetheart, he's here.

1142
01:21:25,784 --> 01:21:27,320
It's Mrs. Parcell.

1143
01:21:27,354 --> 01:21:29,827
Nima, are you ready yet?

1144
01:21:29,859 --> 01:21:32,398
You have to help me
fix my face.

1145
01:21:32,432 --> 01:21:33,435
Okay.

1146
01:21:35,472 --> 01:21:40,649
Today is your day to make
the memories that you want.

1147
01:22:40,004 --> 01:22:42,844
Who gives this woman away?

1148
01:22:42,876 --> 01:22:45,583
She does.

1149
01:22:49,023 --> 01:22:51,294
Well, I mean, I do,

1150
01:22:51,327 --> 01:22:53,399
but, mainly, her.

1151
01:22:53,431 --> 01:22:55,804
<i>We do.</i>

1152
01:22:57,975 --> 01:22:59,712
Okay.

1153
01:23:19,084 --> 01:23:20,989
Sheila!

1154
01:23:32,112 --> 01:23:34,484
This...

1155
01:23:34,516 --> 01:23:36,788
This is really
a beautiful wedding.

1156
01:23:36,822 --> 01:23:39,328
Yeah, it actually is.

1157
01:23:43,068 --> 01:23:44,905
You look wonderful.

1158
01:23:44,939 --> 01:23:46,976
Thank you.
You do, too.

1159
01:23:47,008 --> 01:23:48,747
I love that dress.

1160
01:23:48,779 --> 01:23:50,483
You always did
look good in pink.

1161
01:23:50,516 --> 01:23:53,023
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

1162
01:23:56,529 --> 01:23:58,799
I've really missed you.

1163
01:24:01,638 --> 01:24:04,079
Well, I missed you, too.

1164
01:24:07,818 --> 01:24:09,421
Girl!

1165
01:24:09,455 --> 01:24:12,527
I'm so happy for you.

1166
01:24:12,561 --> 01:24:15,736
She's gorgeous...
And feisty, too!

1167
01:24:15,769 --> 01:24:18,674
Do you know that she hit me?
I heard!

1168
01:24:18,706 --> 01:24:20,010
My god!

1169
01:24:20,043 --> 01:24:21,948
I told her, too, I said,
"I'm gonna get you!"

1170
01:24:21,980 --> 01:24:24,487
I could not believe that
when they told me.

1171
01:24:24,520 --> 01:24:27,057
I am so sorry.
God, that's okay.

1172
01:24:27,091 --> 01:24:28,996
It's quite all right.

1173
01:24:29,029 --> 01:24:32,002
It's so nice
to get to talk to you again.

1174
01:24:32,034 --> 01:24:33,973
I know, you, too.

1175
01:24:38,950 --> 01:24:42,590
We have a last-minute
surprise for the happy couple.

1176
01:24:42,623 --> 01:24:43,928
For their first dance,

1177
01:24:43,960 --> 01:24:45,696
we'd like to serenade
them in style.

1178
01:24:45,729 --> 01:24:48,503
Please let me introduce
the bride's father...

1179
01:24:48,535 --> 01:24:50,906
Mr. Othell Babineaux.

